ZCZC EE24
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 292300 UTC
ON MONDAY EVENING A BROAD AREA OF HIGH PRESSURE IS CENTRED TO THE W OF
DENMARK CENTRAL PRESSURE 1027. A FRONTAL TROUGH LIES TO THE W OF THE BRITISH
ISLES. A SHALLOW LOW LIES OVER NERN IBERIA 1008 MOV N. A SLOW MOV LOW LIES
TO THE SW OF ICELAND. ON TUESDAY THE ICELAND LOW STAYS SLOW MOV AND STARTS
TO FILL AS THE FRONTAL TROUGH MOVS SLWY E TO LIE JUST W OF IRELAND. THE
IBERIAN LOW THEN MOVS NE IN NERN FRANCE AS THE EERN HIGH MOVS E. ON WEDNESDAY
THE FRONTAL TROUGH TO THE W AND IBERIAN LOW MOV N COMBINE INTO A COMPLEX
AREA OF LOW PRESSURE CENTRED JUST S OF IRELAND. DURING THURSDAY THE LOW
TO THE S OF IRELAND MOVS N. GALES ARE POSS FOR SHANNON SOLE AND NERN FITZROY
ON WEDNESDAY THEN FASTNET ON THURSDAY
NNNN